<GmapID>0x80c333b1ebaecb01:0x61a5b96610fbfa2c< /GmapID>< review>
This is a pretty new badminton/ table tennis (ping pong) gym. It switched ownership once since it was opened. The gym is well maintained. It was very cleaned, especially the bathroom! The mats for badminton were in great condition that my friends did not complain about having pain on their knees after their games!

They have a sauna room that is shared by both male and female. It was on timer, so it will take a little while to warm the room up. There were simple gym equipments upstairs for people who wants to workout!

The only thing I want to complain is that this place is cold during winter! What I did was going to the sauna room to keep myself warm in between my badminton games!</review>

< Review>
When I first walked into Arena Badminton some months ago it was a sparkling clean attractive new facility. It had air conditioning, a sauna, a separate gym and bright lights. Thereâ€™s a water fountain for drinks and/or filling your water bottle with filtered water. It was actually exciting to see such a nice place for badminton lovers. Some players liked the new badminton courts but others complained the playing surface was too hard. But nonetheless it was a major improvement over the old dilapidated and  seriously neglected facilities nearby at SGVBC.
However as lately it seems the management and or owners have become overwhelmed by the upkeep of the place. The air conditioning isnâ€™t working well and the entire building is very warm even before the hot spell. But at least there seems to be some cooling which was way better than SGVBC where one risked themselves and their children to heat stroke. Arena is not there yet but still it can be stifling and uncomfortable. The courts themselves seem to be well maintained but not other areas in the building. It seems the other parts of the building are suffering the same neglect as the building at SGVBC. The toilets in bathrooms are already having problems with getting back up and broken and it seems it takes quite a while to get them repaired. There havenâ€™t been any paper towels on the dispenser for weeks. And the windows in the lobby havenâ€™t been cleaned for a long time the same as the mirrors in the bathroom. There is no cafe like the wonderful Indonesian/Chinese place they had at SGVBC. They had the best nasi goreng Iâ€™ve ever tasted.  But unfortunately it appears the owners did not consider their plight at all when they closed shop there. Rumor has it that they were given extremely short notice, like maybe a week or two, before their livelihood was ripped from them. At any rate there seems to be enough room at Arena for a small cafe like this but of course that would take some investment and time. There is a vending machine in the lobby but that hasnâ€™t worked for weeks now. And they also had frozen juice bars but the freezer is just sitting in the corner now also out of service for weeks.
The parking is ample here. They had beautiful shade baring trees throughout the lot but a few weeks ago the tree trimmers butchered them and they no longer produce the same shade and look stunted and sick. There are still talk trees on the perimeters however if youâ€™re concerned about sap and dew dripping onto your car you might not want to park near them. Also beware that the road and the 60 freeway is right there and both are heavily travelled by trucks. It is extremely dusty. Your car will actually be covered in oily dust within ten minutes so consider parking at the side of the building rather than near the street.
This is such a new and beautiful place. I truly hope it can be kept up and not fall into the rot that became SGVBC, for the sake of all the players and all the children who are also training here.<//Review>

<Rating>5< /Rating><Review>I trained with Anthony N. for 6 months and had the best experience at Perform For Life. Prior to starting, I had been recovering from a series of injuries to both my lower and upper half of my body, so I was a out of shape and had only finished my Physical Therapy a few months prior. After completing the assessment, I was paired up with Anthony N. who had also suffered from a shoulder injury before - and was well equipped with in his expertise on how to get my mobility and strength back. Anthony took his time with me, and was careful to not overwork certain problem areas until my body could handle it. This is not to say Anthony went easy on me when I did have the strength, but I appreciate Anthony's patience in allowing my body to grow at a safe pace. I highly recommend Perform For Life (regardless of the location) if you are somehow who is looking for an intimate training session with a knowledgeable fitness specialist, or looking for a small group training class that is not 30+ people piled into a room.

<gmap_id>0x8085809ff89c7e1d:0x68a7acd3a3e45dc6<//gmap_id><Resp>{'time': 1502913334668, 'text': "Sam, we are so proud of you and what you've accomplished in your journey.  Thank you for trusting us with your care! Coach Amber is beyond proud to have helped you with your evolved relationship with health and fitness.  We wish you continued success and say hello to Ella for us!"}< /Resp>< user_name>
Sam Geffner<//user_name>
<user>106819911432904458614< /user>< text>
Recently I told Amber how pleased I was with our work together.  Through my work with her over the months, I have begun to make the transition from a person who had to go to exercise to help improve the odds of keeping my cancer in check, to a person who is beginning to think of exercise as a part of my personality and a valued lifestyle choice.
Amber shows unusual skill in gauging the exercises to my ability.  It often seems as if she starts a set of exercises with a low-ball warm-up resistance.  In subsequent sets I get to request more weight.  That experience of wanting to do more, to work harder is, for me, a unique experience around exercise.   By low-balling resistance and working up, Amber models and teaches a kind of patience that I had never associated with exercise and allows me to experience a quite novel experience in myself of eagerness around exercise combined with patience about the results.  Despite my impatience with her cautious approach, I often wind up feeling manageable muscle soreness after workouts which makes me feel just a bit of the self-righteous and heroic warrior.

Amber shows unexpected inventiveness in hitting the same basic muscle groups in novel ways as well as a consistency of attention to proper form which is unaccustomed to me.  This keeps my workouts interesting and also works all possible associated peripheral muscles. It also contributes to the impression that she really thinks hard about how to make the workouts interesting and entertaining.  She is also so consistent about monitoring the basics of good body mechanics that I now anticipate the corrections she is about to make.  This makes it easier to integrate our training into my daily activity.  For example, I now experience brisk walking as an exercise in awareness in balancing the demands on my legs and calves with my buttocks and back chain.  When lifting, I remind myself to anchor my lats and pay attention to not over-stressing my shoulder joints.  Over the months, my posture has greatly improved, and friends tell me that I am looking much stronger.

Amber is unexpectedly organized in the way that she presents her exercises. She typically starts with warm-ups, presents the main core of our workouts in in sets of 2 or 3 exercises targeting opposing muscle groups, each set repeated three times before moving on to the next set.  She finishes with some playful cool-downs and balance exercises.  This gives me a way to think about the structure of a workout session which has been very helpful to me in beginning to explore working out at home.

Amber's personality and attitudes present a good fit with my personality needs, which has been very helpful in encouraging me to think of exercise as an enjoyable part of my lifestyle.  She is professional about maintaining some distance between her needs and mine, yet not so distant that I don't feel that I have come to know her as a person and feel a sense of her genuine caring and playfulness.  She has skillfully managed all the negative personality traits and unproductive attitudes that I brought to exercise.  For example, each workout she cheerfully and genuinely encourages me to complain about whatever is interfering with my desire to exercise - and then tells me to get going.  She models using one's body with all its limitations as best as one can at the time.  Again and again, I have had the experience of coming in grumpy and unmotivated and leaving feeling energized and successful.  An experienced exerciser may take this for granted, but believe me, this experience is unaccustomed in my life, especially as I have aged and since my cancer treatment.

To the extent possible, I think that Amber brings a quality of broad knowledge, professional attitudes, consistent effort, and playfulness  to our workouts that encourages me to think about my daily activities as potential opportunities to reinforce my workouts and to gladly integrate exercise more deeply into my life.  And that is what Perform for Life is all about.<//text>

<GmapID>0x80db6f4585e343e5:0x7a4ab656afbe6407<//GmapID><Rating>4<//Rating><Text>I'm giving this four stars, honestly, out of nostalgia. And hope.  This was, at one point, a lovely theater. That time has long since passed.  There's been a few changing of hands in the last couple decades and it's now owned by what I believe is a non-profit preservation society.  Which is for the best. This isn't an IMAX theater.  It's an ooold theater. But old in the best way, with velvet curtains around the screen, crazy comfortable seats and bathrooms so old the lettering is in an art deco font.

I've seen some great movies here: Pulp Fiction, The Nightmare Before Christmas, The Dark Knight, and the greatest movie ever made: Raiders of the Lost Ark.  (It even had a teaser trailer for REVENGE of the Jedi!) The side building even used to be my favorite comic book shop!  So yeah, nostalgia plays a big part here.  But it is lovely. And I honestly believe that some day it'll be the five stars I want it to be.<//Text>< UserId.>

< Text>
On September 16th, 2020, I ordered SoundRight Surround Curtains, and a SoundRight Two-Toned Diamond (a wall accent).  At the time I placed the order, the estimated shipping time was 6-8 weeks.  A long time, I thought, but OK.  In November, when nothing arrived, I called and was told that it would take them an additional 8 weeks!  I figured with the pandemic, maybe that was to be expected.  Still, 4 months to ship from the time of my order seemed like a lot.

I donâ€™t recall the exact delivery date, but I would guess it was around late January (within the revised delivery period).  The curtains came and were perfect!  Exactly as they looked on the website and as I ordered.  However, the diamond wall accent came in the wrong color.  I called them to report the problem.  They asked for photos, which I provided (along with the color swatches that Iâ€™d sent for prior to my order).  They acknowledged the error and promised to send me a replacement in the correct color.

That part was all great customer service.  The part that went off the rails was the expected delivery date was JUNE!!!  I got the confirmation of the correction order on February 2, 2021 and it arrived in June!

Better customer service would have prioritized the correction a customer had already waited 16 weeks for, especially for this little thing, which couldnâ€™t take very long to make.

THE BEST PART: The replacement I received in June, was the same wrong color they originally sent!

When I called to complain, they again acknowledged the screw up.  They now promise that this time, theyâ€™ll get the replacement sent correctly.  However, having waited roughly 8 months at this point, I asked for my money back.  That request was completely ignored.  If their track record holds, I suppose I'll see the replacement sometime in October (11 months after I originally ordered).

The right thing to do would be to refund my money and send the correct replacement anyway.  Especially since the thing is made out of corrugated plastic, some foam, fabric, staples and glue.  It couldnâ€™t cost much to produce.

Bottom line: I would not purchase anything from these guys in the future.  Mistakes happen.  Itâ€™s how you handle them, or donâ€™t that separates you from everyone else. At this point, I feel I got lucky with the curtains.</Text>

<review>We ordered a row of 3 Diamante seats, and two individual recliners. The ordering process, delivery and setup were excellent and the chairs are highly functional. Clara was very helpful to work with and help pick the right seats. The seats look fantastic, are solidly built, and the motor mechanism seem to be reliable. My only issue - we set up our family room as our entertainment room so these chairs get used daily. The cushioning isn't as thick/luxurious as you might expect for a conventional recliner for your family room. They are kind of skimpy on cushioning. I notice this because I'm getting old & grumpy and my lower back sometimes feels it.  If I could knock a half star for this I would but its not worth knocking a whole star. <user>110832578776887653815<//user><Name>Legairre Radden</Name><Date>1614440360608< /Date><rate>5</rate><Review>If I could give 10 stars instead of 5 I would.  Our sales rep was Bob Wheelan, and Bob did an incredible job before the sale of explaining all the options and different chairs and sofas. Bob answered every question and knew everything about the different kinds of seating they offer.  Not only was Bob great before the sale, but there was a snow storm that caused our seating to take 17 days to get to us.  During that time Bob contacted the shipping company several times and helped get the shipment moving again after it had been sitting in Philly for almost a week.

For our theaters front row we went with a row of 3 Mantra sofa, that has 3 recliners, then added 2 removable  slide arm armrest so we could have a sofa when we wanted and separate seating for movie nights. For our back row we went with a row of 2 Mantra seats.

The Mantra seats are very well built with finished backs and full leather all around.  The seats have powered headrest, powered lumbar, and power recline, and also have base lighting, lighted cupholders, and sound shakers.  The quality and attention to detail in the seats is just great. The seats are incredibly comfortable and I'd say the seats are a medium firmness  and have completely change movie nights.

The seats came in 5 boxes on 2 pallets and the boxes are huge and the seats are heavy so get a buddy to help.  Seriously each seat weighed about 140lbs and the double arm recliner that makes up half of our row of 2 weighed even more.

I can't say enough about my experience before, during or after buying the seats except ask for Bob.  He'll take care of you and you won't regret your purchase.<//Review>< Pics>

I had visited a couple of high-end furniture stores in my area looking for something nice and within my budget. I found the perfect set, but the price was astronomical. ONE row of 3 seats was more than what I paid for TWO rows of 3 seats from 4seating (when you include the furniture store's cost of delivery and set up)!

So after I concluded that 4seating's price was right, my next concern was quality. I searched the internet for all of the information I could find about Seatcraft as a manufacturer and specifically the Venetian seats I wanted to buy. Everything I read was positive with the exception of the LED lights underneath being a bit too bright. That's a small problem with a few easy solutions. So my wife and I did the unthinkable. We ordered seats we never sat on based only on reviews like the one you're reading now. The end result is me being such a satisfied customer I felt compelled to tell the world. My seats arrived early and in excellent condition. Everything was well wrapped and there were no missing parts. The instructions couldn't have been easier. It's literally ONE step to assemble.

I can't describe how happy my wife and I were when we put the seats together and sat on them for the first time. Wouldn't you know, these seats feel EXACTLY like the seats we sat on at the high-end furniture store I mentioned earlier. And it's the same top grain leather. I assume the price difference is a result of furniture stores having to pay for showroom space, salespeople, TV and radio advertising, delivery and setup staff, etc. If you're looking to save money, order your seats from 4seating and have a neighbor, a friend, or anyone you can pay in beer help you carry the boxes into your home. < Rating>

< review>
Really good experience ordering online from 4seating! Talked to and ordered from Zack on September 16 and he was very helpful with product information and quite candid - and accurate - about shipping dates. He said that our theater seating would not ship until approximately October 21st (but actually shipped a week earlier) and we received it today - on October 21st. (In this "order today and your stuff will arrive tomorrow"-type of online buying many of us are used to - the shipping date initially seemed a bit far out, but it turns our we needed those weeks to get our space organized and ready for the seating.) The shipping company was also friendly, prompt, and careful in delivering to the curbside. Our chairs were very safely boxed/packaged and were as easy to set up as Zach told us. All of the electrical components seem to work just fine (and there's a surprise USB port on the chairs!) and the chairs are very comfortable. We will have to see how the "gel leather" holds up, but it looks good and hopefully will be easy to wipe clean. We originally thought about choosing the manual controls, but are very glad we went with the power recline - so great to have a huge range of possible reclining positions. No hesitation about ordering again in the future from this company - we're happy customers!<//review>

<username>Dan Lowder</username>< rating>

<review>Great customer service.  I worked with Bob who was knowledgeable and genuinely helpful with great advice.  Excellent product - we love our theater seats!  We ordered one row of them for our theater and after just a few weeks we've enjoyed them so much we are ordering another row.  It really makes movie night feel special with our family and friends.  We have the Seatcraft Venetian chairs.  They fit our space perfectly, the leather is nice and comfortable and the power recline is way fun.  These don't have the power headrest which would be nice but that is more expensive and we find that neck pillows work great if you want to recline further back and keep your head comfortably forward.  The led lights are fun too, but not really practical in a theater room because they are so bright.  I wish they were much dimmer or had a dimmer control as simple as low/medium/high/off setting when you push the button.  That would be practical and probably easy to implement. Something for Seatcraft to think about if they ever read this.    That's a minor complaint and not enough to take away any stars. I found this place online while looking for a four seater sofa with recliners. I called and spoke with Jesse Valderama and he emailed me several options that met my criteria. Jesse was awesome and I would rate him 5 stars for his customer service. The four seats arrived in extra large boxes on a horribly dilapidated pallet that needed several blocks to stay upright. The product has a lot of room for improvement and therefore I believe it is highly overpriced. The swivel tray tables don't allow for a glass to be in the cupholders at the same time. The controls (lumbar, headrest, etc.) are not in an ideal location on some chairs. The placement and location of both of these items could have been much better. Some of the seats arrived with some scuffs and blemishes. Lastly, they are made in Vietnam so take that into consideration when considering craftsmanship and quality control. I would rate the product a 3 out of 5.

Update: 3/25/21

I have left three messages over the last week for the salesman with no answer!   Actually got an answer a couple days ago via email which went to spam for some reason.

I am supposed to buy some leather cleaner to remove the marks that were "for shipping"  !! ??

Seats are very firm and I am hopeful they will soften up with use.
The tray design sucks!!!  It is not possible to put a soda can in the same arm as a tray!  All would be OK if you have separate seats (not attached)
I may have to fabricate some new ones.

If I had been able to try these out before purchase I would not have forked over big bucks< /text>< rate>

<Rate>5<//Rate>< review>
It was a great experience to purchase 6 home theater Seatcraft chairs with the help of Bob Wheelan. We got additional accessories with the help and assistance of Alex Osorio. This is an outstanding company dedicated to making sure their customers get the right product and they enjoy the experience of watching movies at home. I did end up spending more money than initially budgeted, but I applied the all saying of "buy once, but right". The Apex leather 7000 in brown color is like a business class seat, or I should say it is even better than those, even the flat beds. Besides the recliner part, it has neck and lumbar support. Both features are really worth it as you can adjust your view to the screen for all body sizes and shapes. An added feature is the sound shaker subwoofer that comes with the unit. You will need to purchase a separate receiver that works with up to 4 chairs, so in my case I had to buy two for the 6 units. A 7-2 home theater with vibrating chairs gives you the ultimate experience. All my friends want to come over to watch movies. You should see their faces when the action starts to kick in and the chair starts to vibrate. They all say the same â€I need to get a similar set up in my houseâ€. I never write reviews, but I think it is worth putting a good word for the quality products sold by 4seating.com, and their excellent customer service. Both Bob and Alex were extremely knowledgeable about all their products and their features. They will be able to supply you with a great product that fits your needs and budget. My home theater is still a work in progress, as I have only installed the chairs and the movie pictures on the walls. I need to paint the walls and install sound panels to minimize the reverb. You will be hard pressed to find a better product, they seem to be the gold standard and the only game in town. Drop them a call and let them help you.<//review>

<review>11/23/20 update - after posting the review below I received a call from Lynn in customer services. She was extremely kind and understanding and worked with me to find a solution that made me feel fully heard and appreciated as a customer. Thank you Lynn for being so helpful!!

I took a risk in ordering a Seatcraft theater sofa from 4Seating.com without being able to try out the sofa first. The sofa looked nice upon arrival but we immediately realized it was too firm and uncomfortable to use daily. We were really disappointed. Fortunately, we could contact 4seating to take advantage of their satisfaction guarantee. Right? Wrong. < text>

<Name>Awookiee< /Name><Review>I purchased 3 of the Seatcraft Diamante line of seating and I couldn't be happier with the purchase.  I was skeptical ordering online having never seen or sat in them before but their associate Alex Osorio was extremely helpful and answered every question I had.  I first contacted him about a year and a half prior to purchasing the seats asking some initial questions and he was extremely helpful even though I told him it would be about 2 years before I was ready to buy.  He never once pressured me into buying them before I was ready and I am very appreciative of that.

The seating itself is extremely comfortable and to begin with I questioned  whether powered headrests were necessary but ended up getting seating with them.  Very thankful I did as it makes all the difference in the world when you recline in the chairs.  The 7000 series leather is very high quality and I know these chairs will last a long time.

I also purchased the add on Soundshaker amplifier as the seats have the seatshakers preinstalled.  It's something that takes a little fine tuning but adds a lot to the experience.  If you've ever gone to an AMC Dolby theater, this is very similar to what the seating there uses to shake slightly anytime the frequency (Hz) hits the point you have it set at with the amplifier.

All in all I would highly recommend 4seating to anybody lookin for theater style seating.  I obviously can't attest to the longevity of the chairs as I've only had them a couple weeks now but I know these are built to last.  Alex Osorio was a pleasure to work with and I already have 2 neighbors jealous of my chairs and will likely be purchasing some in the near future. <rating>5<//rating><Review>I found 4seating by doing a google search on Movie Room Chairs, and this was the first place I started looking.  Good thing is because this place provided all the support and good prices I needed.  I read some reviews really quick and all reviews were very good (they mentioned Joseph Ybarra).  I don't base my preferences off other reviews, but I was in unfamiliar territory, and needed some advise at the minimum.

I have a smaller movie room that cannot accommodate normal seating.  So I shot an email to the customer service email, and happened to get a very quick reply from Joseph Ybarra.  Joseph sent me several options that would fit my movie room, and answered all my questions.   At this time, I was still unsure of my purchase.   I now fired up the ole google search engine, and compared what Joseph sent me (just for my own sanity).   It wasn't long till I realized I initially contacted the right company (4seating).   Now I was ready for the purchase.

I called and spoke with Joseph on the phone, and we went through all the details needed.   Nothing at all (not even the seats) were pressured, Joseph just provided the information I needed.  I happened to see an option regarding SoundShakers, so I asked Joseph.   Joseph advised that this provides a great movie experience by enhancing the base from within the seats.  Since I don't have a large movie room, I thought this would be a great addition, so I included those on every seat.

Only "issue" I had was it took a little over a month to get the seats (which is totally understandable, and they installed the SoundShakers on all the seats).  I was just being impatient.

Got the seats and had the delivery install same, again, great service.   The instll took about 2 hours and they went through everything with me (expept the SoundShakers, as they hook up to my receiver, and they cannot be responsible).   Again, totally understandable, and this gives me a little pride in part of the installation.

The seats are more than expected.  I got the Seatcraft Napa.   These are very comfortable seats that have electric head rest, which I initially thought was a waste, but completely not, once I was able to experience different head rest positions.    The chairs also come with great accessories, such as the table and cup holders (I didn't have cup holders in my previous seating - because of the size of the room).  The lights in the seat are also an awesome feature.

Anyhow, summary - 4seating is a superb place to shop for movie room seating.  The customer service is top notch and something that is hard to find now-a-days.   The customer service alone would want me to purchase from them, but then you add on the great prices, comfortable selection, and massive options, you cannot go wrong with 4seating.</Review>< pics>

Joe Denning<//user_name>
<time>1601672800987<//time><Rate>1<//Rate>< Review>
Buy locally!!
Purchasing from 4seating was a big mistake for us.  We wanted to and were willing to pay for high quality furniture.  Our first love seat arrived with the armrest bent and out of line.  The center console was built on an leaning forward angle.  Drinks fell out and fell over due to the center console being on a forward leaning angle.

4seating was great, they apologized and told us to keep the poorly build original love seat and they sent us a brand new one at NO COST.

We received the 2nd love seat.  However, to our dismay, the 2nd couch had the exact same problems as the first.  We made contact with 4seating, however, after several attempts, they ignored our emails.  I believe their attitude was you paid $2800 for two love seats, we are done with you and screw you.

We tried to sell the love seats for $1200 a piece to somewhat recoup our investment and purchase quality love seats but unable to get any takers.  So, we are stuck with 2 love seats that you would buy from the "clearance center" or "slightly damaged" or "scratch and dent" section of a store.

We just wanted a quality comfortable love seat and were willing to pay the price for this as you typically get want you pay for.

Disappointed, we should have stuck with LazyBoy.  Also, the seatcrafts are made in wonderful China so beware of the quality.</Review>

UPDATE: We had to return the SeatCraft beautiful power reclining loveseat TWICE, due to damage in shipment. Now after 4 months since we placed the order, we have cancelled it. <text>Joseph Ybarra, the sales agent, has been great to work with.  He helped me find exactly what we were looking for.  A theater loveseat without a center console. We are looking forward to receiving our new Seatcraft Pantheon seats.  I will post photos upon arrival of the furniture.  :)

This is an update on the Theater seats purchased from 4Seating.  We were fooled by the promise of "Ready to Ship".  It took six weeks for the seats to arrive.  When they finally did, we realized that a "row of two loveseat" is in fact two separate chairs pushed together, not a loveseat at all. Then, one of the seats was defective.  The "white glove" delivery team had us accept the delivery and referred us to 4seating. I promptly contacted Joseph, who referred me to Customer Service.  I sent an email, describing  the problem and was contacted 24 hours later.  I was asked to send a bunch of photos and video of the issue and after two days of discussions we were told a replacement chair would be sent.

Another six weeks later, the "white glove" delivery team picked up the defective chair and proceded to set up the replacement chair, which -  was defective as well.   Still no lumbar support, still no working lights.

In order to connect the light strip, the 'white glove deliver team' fully reclined the chair that had been working until then, connected the light strip, which shorted out the light strips and the cup holder lights on both chairs, AND the chair that was working until then, is now NOT WORKING at all. In fact, it remains in a fully reclined position with the headrest fully extended.  We did not want to accept delivery of yet another defective chair, but the "white glove" delivery team simply left without our signatures.

I promptly contacted Joseph again, who again referred me to customer support.  I again emailed photos, described what happened and ... NO RESPONSE for days.   It took a second inquiry regarding the status of my email for a customer service rep by the name of Lynn to call.  Lynn was very kind and empathetic and told me that they would have to order replacement parts...  Why do I have to wait for replacement parts on a purchase of NEW CHAIRS??   She assured me that replacement parts will resolve the issues and I was to call as soon as the parts arrived so she could schedule someone to come do the repairs.

I have since received an email announcing delivery of replacement parts sometime in January of 2021.

In the meantime, we have two defective theater seats sitting in our media room, one of which cannot be used at all.  I have not been able to receive any feedback from a person since I have voiced my dissatisfaction about the lack of customer support.

{'time': 1592636596389, 'text': 'Hi Robert, thank you for your feedback. Looking forward to help you on your second purchase.'}<//Response>
<username>Robert</username><review>Ordered this on Monday 4/20 after speaking with Zachary from Seatcraft. Wife and I originally had our sights set on the Europa, but Zachary suggested the Anthem as its made of top grain leather where as the Europa is made of gel leather. Same features on both and not much difference in price for a much better material. It was great advice which we followed.

I placed the order and Zachary told me the item will ship on 4/21 to a local mover near me and they would contact me in a day or two after they received it to schedule delivery.  I opted not to do the white glove service as Iâ€™m handy with assembling furniture, and Zachary said that although the couch was heavy, the backrests were not attached and could be carried individually, two people should be able to manage carrying the base. Based on that guidance, I went with curbside drop. If I can offer advice: For the love of God and all that is holy, do NOT do curbside delivery. The couch is incredibly heavy. If your situation requires carrying the couch up or down stairs, pay the 199 bucks and have them do the heavy work. I wound up hiring local movers last minute to come and move it. Also, the love seat comes wrapped in lots of cardboard and is placed on a large wooden pallet.  The driver did not take the pallet, so I had the fun of breaking down the pallet into a whole bunch of pieces to ensure it fit inside the trash bins (we have strict trash/recycling requirements here).  Had I done the white glove service I would not have had to mess with all of that.  So again - buy the white glove service, totally worth it.

About the delivery schedule itself, remember I said Zachary told me to expect a call from the delivery company? That never happened. Dude just arrived on Wednesday 4/22 and I was totally unprepared. It made for a long and inconvenient afternoon sitting outside guarding my new couch chillin on the sidewalk while waiting for last minute hired movers to arrive. So not very happy about the delivery experience.

Couch itself: Pretty comfortable and enjoy it a lot. But some annoying small defects. 1. Seam on back of couch has a two inch defect where the threads are frayed/missing. 2. The leather is sagging where it should sit flush and tight under the center power console (on fold out middle table). 3. The post that secures the armrest table into the armrest kept popping out, making the table unusable.

Warranty support and customer service is great.  They answered the phone on the first call and kept in close communication with my by e-mail.  For issue 1, they are sending me a new seat back (will take  few weeks but I'm ok with that).  For issues 2 and 3, they provided me guidance by e-mail on how to fix myself.  Very simple and quick fixes.  If you can use a screw driver, you can fix these issues in under 5 minutes.

Also, if buying made in the USA is important to you, then you may be unhappy.  Although Seatcraft appears to be a U.S. owned and operated company, it appears my recliner couch was made in Vietnam (as per the manufacturer label affixed to the bottom of my couch).  Not a show stopper for me.

Overall, its a very good product, quite comfortable and the accessories are very nice.  Some shoddy workmanship on the finishing touches are frustrating, but their warranty support and quick response has been very good. The delivery service could have been better, but I realize they outsource that part. Had the delivery experience been better, I would have rated at 5 stars.  Overall, this is a great company to do business with, and I would buy furniture from them again.< /review></record>

<userid>110547807011159906372< /userid>< username>
Mark Holmes<//username>
<Date>1565895779921<//Date><Rate>5< /Rate><text>I've never bought a piece of furniture online before. It seems crazy to buy a couch without sitting in it. However, we had a specific need for a couch that swiveled on its base and was big enough for two people. The cuddle couch by 4seating exactly matched our specifications, so we took the risk.

Anna Hernandez dealt with our order and she was really great. She sent us cloth samples to choose from. We chose our colors and material and called her back to place the order. She had a direct line, so it was easy to do. We received an email confirmation of our order.

It took several weeks to manufacture the couch and ottoman, but we were in no hurry. Since we live in a high rise condo, deliveries have to be scheduled and elevators padded in preparation, so we ordered the white glove delivery service. Before the promised date, we received an email stating the couch was at the delivery agent and we should call to schedule. It was easy to do. My wife talked to a person and explained the restrictions. The delivery company was very accommodating. On the day of delivery, I was unavailable, but my wife accepted delivery. She said it went smoothly and the delivery guys were helpful.

Ok, nothing is perfect. 4Seating does business online and like all of us, rely on partners. Things occasionally go wrong and what separates great companies from ones you regret doing business with is how they deal with problems. When I got home I saw the couch. It looked great, but I immediately noticed a large scrape that my wife had totally missed. I have no idea if it was done in manufacture, storage, or delivery, but there it was and my wife had signed the delivery notice saying everything was in order. I immediately called and emailed Anna and left a message, but then I looked at the couch thinking, "This just doesn't seem right. Im not sure I'd have ordered this color, though I must say it goes well with the cherry floors and other furniture." I looked at the original order and yes, the color was wrong.

Next morning, I received a call back and an email from Anna saying she'd passed my information and photos to John Jasso in customer service. Part of me was thinking, "Oh no, here we go." But, almost immediately my phone rang and it was John. The only question he asked was whether the box was damaged. I told him I wasn't there, but my wife said the box was gone when they brought it through the door of our unit. He said he would email a resolution in a few minutes. Within a few minutes he told me they were sending a replacement. The only question he asked was did we want them to make the original choice and replace the couch and ottoman or make just the couch in the delivered color. We went with the delivered color. He explained without asking that it would match the ottoman because the material maker always sent advance notice of a dye batch change. Lastly, he said they were expediting manufacture to two or three weeks and the delivery company would remove the old one.

Right now, I'm relaxing on this luxurious furniture item writing this review and sipping a scotch. The only reason I have not giving the review 5 stars is we have yet to resolve the issue, but when done I'll revise the review to five stars. I don't know where the mix up in color occurred, but guess we were lucky in that what we have is better than what we specified. Anna and John were excellent and I would assume from their attitude that 4seating is an ethical company throughout.

Edited to 5 stars after successfully replaced. Thanks!<//text><Pictures>None<//Pictures><response>None<//response>< gmapID>

< Text>
Be warned that many of these reviews are fake. This company struggles greatly in providing any kind of service. They are focused on making money and don't care at all about the customer. Watch out for Richard Valdez. He has no desire to help anyone and doesn't care who you are.

I purchased home theater chairs and while the site advertises many features they don't tell you all the parts you need. They will charge you for the chairs and even deliver them without all the parts. Then when they show up they act like it's a shipping or packaging issue. When you call in they tell you that you didn't buy all the right parts and make you go to their website to figure it out. They won't tell you what's missing they just send you a link to their site and make you get and figure it out.

Since the chairs are already delivered you're stuck paying for shipping to return the order and any additional fees they add on our you are forced to go online and buy the missing parts, if you can figure it out.

On top of all this nightmare the accessories are cheap and don't work. You pay $50 for an LED light and it's cheap plastic that is non functional. You're then stuck fighting with the poor customer service department to try and get a replacement. It took me 5-6 different emails to try to make any progress.

As if this wasn't bad enough, once I figured out what to buy I ordered the extra parts. I then received a notice that everything I previously ordered plus the missing parts is being shipped. The invoice only had the missing parts but now it says I have four new chairs coming. I REFUSE to pay for the new chairs and dread the hassle I'll have trying to figure it out. I tried to call in and their support staff told me they don't know what is going on and that I should call in tomorrow and see if someone else answers the phone as maybe they can figure it out. Once again this company doesnt care at all about customers.

While the chairs seem nice, the experience, horrific customer service, poor ordering system, crappy website, and general catastrophic business processes have made this a nightmare experience.

Thank you "4 seating" for ruining my birthday / Father's day present and something I've saved up for for a long time.

DO NOT BUY HERE! If you do, good luck and consider yourself warned!</Text>

< review>
I bought the Seatcraft Venetian Love Console Recliner.  It is a row of 3 chairs, separated by 2 consoles that drop down; this way I can lay across the couch if I want, but I can also have arm rests inbetween each seat as well if desired.  I also purchased a 5 year warranty ($177) and got $300 off for memorial day weekend.  It was delivered promptly and the gentleman was very nice about getting the couch right up to my door (I did not purchase white glove delivery but had friends bring it in for me).  The couch is great, apart for not coming with brackets to link the couches together.  They are currently on standby but the customer service (I had Fernando) was very responsive and willing to work through the minor issues I had.  Very good customer service.  I also didn't have light across the console seats, so those are going to be sent to me as well.< /review>

The USB is unusable due to the location. There is nothing to connect the chairs together. So, they are rarely aligned. The company recommends looking on EBAY for brackets that might work. < review>
An outstanding experience with 4Seating!

I was lucky enough to be on a business trip only 15 minutes away from their location.  I stopped by and met  Alex.  He was terrific.  Took his time, let me sit in every chair, answered all my questions and gave me a great deal.

I wound up ordering 2x front row Seatcraft Monterey Black Leather Power LAF Recliners and 2x back row of the same.

These seats are wonderful.  I'm coming from Berkline powered recliners and these are every bit as comfortable and the powered headrest is awesome.  They are also faster to recline than the Berkline's and quieter as well.   I just wished there was a way to have my Media Room continue to smell like the leather from these seats.  It's wonderful!

The seats came packaged very well and in perfect condition.  There was a small issue with the phone/tablet holder which was quickly resolved by 4Seating with a replacement on it's way.

Can't say enough about this company, the service, Alex, and the seats themselves.

Looking forward to adding more!<//review>

<userid>111718219772148104845</userid>< username>
Allan Douglas-Braid<//username>
<Time>1513731135284</Time><rate>4<//rate>< Text>
Ordered row of four Barcalounger Solaris seats - excellent seats, highly recommended. Found a small tear on the back on an armrest, 4Seating was quick to respond without fuss, and has shipped out a replacement.  Customer service was excellent.  Pulled one star for misleading sales practices - Seats are prominently advertised as being equipped with Sound Shaker technology that " vibrates the chair in sync with the on-screen action!"  - except that it doesn't, because you need additional Sound Shaker equipment to make it work. In other words, the seats are equipped with only one part of the sound shaker system, parts that do absolutely nothing on their own - you need to buy the additional Sound Shaker amplifier (several hundred dollars) and nowhere, anywhere, can I find anything that says so.  The site lists the seats as equipped with "Sound Shaker", and gives you every indication (including a video)  that the sound shaker system is a complete functioning feature, when in reality, the seats are only equipped with the traducers,  useless items on their own that will not work without additional costly parts. This is deceptive and unnecessary -  having the transducers is worthwhile if you plan to have the sound shaker system, but 4Seating should be more upfront and forthcoming with what you are actually getting.<//Text>

< text>
In April 2017 we purchased the Seatcraft Sierra Cream Leather 7000 Power Straight Row of 3 theater seating. When they arrived, the boxes were a little beat up but once unpacked and set up in our room they are beautiful. We absolutely love them. However a couple weeks ago one of the chairs stopped power reclining and we were initially a bit upset due to the cost of the chairs and the quick malfunction. We placed a call to 4seating and have been in contact with account representative John Jasso who has been amazing to work with. Not only did he try to help get the chair fixed quickly via helpful instructions, but once he realized it was a not fixable, he sent out the replacement part quickly and apologetically. Mr. Jasso also followed up with us not only by email but follow up phone calls as well. Being in Customer Service for many years, I am extremely satisfied with Mr. Jasso and 4seating for fixing the malfunction in my chair. I strongly suggest purchasing the warranty for piece of mind and also if ordering the Soundshaker kit, make sure you ask for the install instructions. We have not been able to install our kit as we are still waiting for the instructions to be mailed to us as they were inadvertently left out of the original order.<//text>
